## Workflow

Bobby uses a ticket-based workflow with frontmatter-based stages:

```
backlog → planning → building → reviewing → testing → shipping → done
```

Tickets live in `<%= tickets_dir %>/` — stage is tracked in ticket.md frontmatter.
Blocked tickets have `blocked: true` in frontmatter with a reason.

## Safety Rules

<safety_rules>
All agents must follow these rules. Violations are treated as critical failures.

**Never run destructive commands:**
- `rm -rf` or `rm -r` on directories outside the ticket's scope
- `DROP TABLE`, `DROP DATABASE`, `TRUNCATE` or any destructive SQL
- `git push --force` or `git push -f` (use `--force-with-lease` if rebase is needed)
- `git reset --hard` (use `git stash` or `git checkout -- <file>` for targeted reverts)
- `git clean -fd` or `git clean -fx`
- `docker system prune`, `docker volume rm`
- `kill -9` on unknown processes
- `chmod -R 777` or `chown -R` on system directories
- Any command with `sudo` unless the plan explicitly requires it

**Never modify outside your scope:**
- Do not edit files unrelated to the current ticket
- Do not change CI/CD configuration unless the ticket explicitly requires it
- Do not modify environment files (.env, credentials, secrets)
- Do not install global packages or change system-level config

**Always verify before acting:**
- Run `git diff --stat` before committing to review what changed
- Run tests before marking work complete
- Check `git status` after every commit to confirm clean state
</safety_rules>

## Working Style

- Read referenced files before forming opinions or writing code. Do not speculate about code you have not opened.
- When multiple files need to be read, read them in parallel to save time.
- Commit all changed files before marking work complete. A clean `git status` is required after every stage.
- Provide evidence for claims: test output, screenshots, API responses. Assertions without evidence are not accepted.
- Implement exactly what the plan specifies. Prefer minimal solutions over overengineered ones.
- **Always use `bobby create` to make tickets.** Never write ticket files or the `.counter` file manually — the CLI handles frontmatter structure, slug generation, counter atomicity, and starter `test-cases.md`.
- **Never suppress errors** in bobby commands (no `2>/dev/null`, no `|| true`). If a command fails, investigate the cause.
- **The ticket stage is the sole progress tracker.** Do not create separate task/todo lists to track pipeline progress — read `ticket.md` frontmatter to know what stage a ticket is in.

## Pipeline

- **Fast mode:** `bobby run pipeline TKT-001` — auto-chains all agents
- **Slow mode:** `bobby run next TKT-001` — runs next agent for current stage
- **Batch mode:** `bobby run plan` (no ticket ID) — runs agent on all tickets in stage
- **Ship:** `bobby run ship` — creates PR, merges, moves to done
- **Named pipeline:** `bobby run pipeline TKT-001 --pipeline thorough` — uses a named pipeline from `.bobbyrc.yml`

### Custom Pipelines

Define named pipelines in `.bobbyrc.yml`:

```yaml
pipelines:
  default: [plan, build, review, test]
  thorough: [plan, build, review, security, test]
  quick: [plan, build, test]
```

## Agents

### Planner (bobby-plan)
When told to "plan", "refine", or "brainstorm", load `<%= paths.skills %>/bobby-plan/SKILL.md`.
- **Epic mode**: breaks big ideas into child tickets
- **Refine mode**: creates plan.md + test-cases.md for a ticket

### Builder (bobby-build)
When told to "build" or "work tickets", load `<%= paths.skills %>/bobby-build/SKILL.md`.
- TDD red-green-refactor cycle
- Commits code to current branch

### Reviewer (bobby-review)
When told to "review", load `<%= paths.skills %>/bobby-review/SKILL.md`.
- Reviews git diff + acceptance criteria
- Separate agent from build for fresh perspective

### Tester (bobby-test)
When told to "test", load `<%= paths.skills %>/bobby-test/SKILL.md`.
- Tests through the **live running app** (browser, API calls) — never runs specs (build/review already did that)

### Shipper (bobby-ship)
When told to "ship", load `<%= paths.skills %>/bobby-ship/SKILL.md`.
- Creates PR, waits for CI, merges

### UX Designer (bobby-ux)
When told to "review design" or "UX audit", load `<%= paths.skills %>/bobby-ux/SKILL.md`.
- Reviews live app through Chrome browser — never reads source code

### Product Manager (bobby-pm)
When told to "PM review" or "product review", load `<%= paths.skills %>/bobby-pm/SKILL.md`.
- Reviews live app, identifies UX gaps and feature opportunities

### Security Auditor (bobby-security)
When told to "security audit" or "security review", load `<%= paths.skills %>/bobby-security/SKILL.md`.
- OWASP Top 10 + STRIDE threat modeling on changed code
- Only flags findings with 8/10+ confidence and concrete exploit scenarios

### Debugger (bobby-debug)
When told to "debug" or "investigate", load `<%= paths.skills %>/bobby-debug/SKILL.md`.
- Systematic root-cause debugging: Reproduce → Hypothesize → Trace → Verify → Fix
- Scope-locked: only fixes the bug, never refactors

### Documentation (bobby-docs)
When told to "update docs" or "document release", load `<%= paths.skills %>/bobby-docs/SKILL.md`.
- Updates README, CLAUDE.md, CHANGELOG after shipping
- Only changes documentation that is now stale

### Performance (bobby-performance)
When told to "benchmark" or "check performance", load `<%= paths.skills %>/bobby-performance/SKILL.md`.
- Measures page load times, resource sizes, request counts
- Compares against baseline, flags regressions

### Watchdog (bobby-watchdog)
When told to "watchdog check" or "verify deploy", load `<%= paths.skills %>/bobby-watchdog/SKILL.md`.
- Post-deploy health verification: page loads, console errors, API responses
- Files critical bugs for any failures

## Learnings

Each skill has a `learnings.md` file that accumulates anti-patterns. Always check learnings before starting work.

## Bobby CLI Commands

```
bobby create -t "Title" --type bug -p high   # Create ticket
bobby create -t "Epic" --epic                # Create epic (breaks down)
bobby list                                   # Show board
bobby list --blocked                         # Show blocked tickets
bobby view TKT-001                           # View ticket
bobby view TKT-001 --plan                    # View plan
bobby move TKT-001 review                   # Move to reviewing
bobby move TKT-001 reject "reason"          # Reject back to building
bobby move TKT-001 block "reason"           # Block ticket
bobby move TKT-001 unblock                  # Unblock ticket
bobby run next TKT-001                      # Slow mode: next agent for stage
bobby run pipeline TKT-001                  # Fast mode: auto-chain all agents
bobby run plan                              # Batch: plan all tickets in planning
bobby run ship                              # Ship all ready tickets
bobby run ux                                # Freeform UX design review
bobby run pm                                # Freeform PM product review
bobby run security TKT-001                  # Security audit (OWASP + STRIDE)
bobby run debug TKT-001                     # Root-cause debugging
bobby run docs                              # Update docs after shipping
bobby run performance                              # Performance benchmarking
bobby run watchdog                            # Post-deploy health check
bobby retro TKT-001 "pattern"              # Create retrospective
bobby retro --weekly                        # Weekly retro with metrics
bobby learn bobby-build "pattern" "desc"    # Add learning
bobby upgrade                               # Upgrade Bobby to latest version
```
